    "transcript": "The garden had been abandoned for decades, but it refused to die. Roses climbed the iron gate, their thorns locking it shut. Ivy covered the stone walls like a second skin.\n\nAnd at the center, where a fountain had once stood, a single apple tree grew crooked and wild, its branches heavy with fruit that no one picked. Birds came and went. Seasons turned. The garden kept its own time, answering to no one.",
